---
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ItemCard from "../../../components/ItemCard.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const pkgs = (await getCollection("packages"))
  .filter((p) => p.data.subkind === "skill")
  .sort((a, b) => a.data.name.localeCompare(b.data.name));
---
<Layout
  title="Claude Code skills on Flox — packaged, pinned, one-line install"
  description="Every Claude Code skill packaged for Flox — domain-specific capability bundles like writing, coding, and shell utilities. Each one Nix-pinned and reproducible."
>
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Skills</h1>
  <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500">{pkgs.length} skills</p>
  <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
    Skills are domain-specific capability bundles for Claude Code — packaged
    prompts, scripts, and configurations that give an agent specific
    expertise. The packages on this page wrap each skill as a Flox-installable,
    Nix-pinned bundle so a team gets identical agent behavior across every
    developer's machine. Add a skill via
    <code class="font-mono text-sm">flox/skill-&lt;name&gt;</code> in any
    manifest's <code class="font-mono text-sm">[install]</code> block.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
    Skills differ from plugins in scope: a plugin extends the agent
    runtime (MCP servers, command palettes, IDE hooks) while a skill is
    a tightly-scoped knowledge or workflow bundle. A skill might teach the
    agent how to write release notes for your team's specific format,
    how to triage incidents using your runbook, or how to apply your
    company's house style to documentation. Packaging skills as Flox
    bundles is the same trick as plugins — version-locked, manifest-included,
    reproducible. Bring up a fresh laptop, run <code class="font-mono text-xs">flox activate</code>,
    and the same agent with the same skills is ready to go.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
    All skills listed below pair with <a href={`${base}envs/claude/`} class="underline">flox/claude</a>,
    which materializes skill manifests into the agent's config tree on
    activation. No copy-pasting prompts between machines, no drift between
    a developer's local skills and the CI runner's.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-8 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    {pkgs.map((p) => (
      <ItemCard
        kind="pkg"
        subkind="skill"
        name={p.data.name}
        title={p.data.title}
        tagline={p.data.tagline}
        href={`${base}packages/${p.data.name}/`}
        ai_role={p.data.ai_role}
      />
    ))}
  </div>
</Layout>
